Overview: In November 2021 Ireland exported €15.3B and imported €9.87B, resulting in a positive trade balance of €5.39B. Between November 2020 and November 2021 the exports of Ireland have increased by €547M (3.72%) from €14.7B to €15.3B, while imports increased by €944M (10.6%) from €8.92B to €9.87B.
Exports: The top exports of Ireland are Blood, antisera, vaccines, toxins and cultures ($32.6B), Nitrogen Heterocyclic Compounds ($27.8B), Packaged Medicaments ($27.8B), Integrated Circuits ($10B), and Scented Mixtures ($8.68B), exporting mostly to United States ($53.7B), Belgium ($19B), Germany ($18.5B), United Kingdom ($17.7B), and China ($10.2B).
In: 2019, Ireland was the world's biggest exporter of Nitrogen Heterocyclic Compounds ($27.8B), Scented Mixtures ($8.68B), Sulfonamides ($4.68B), and Nucleic Acids ($4.43B)
Imports: The top imports of Ireland are Planes, Helicopters, and/or Spacecraft ($7.64B), Computers ($3.74B), Packaged Medicaments ($3.35B), Refined Petroleum ($3.35B), and Blood, antisera, vaccines, toxins and cultures ($3.28B), importing mostly from United Kingdom ($26.9B), United States ($14.4B), Germany ($8.77B), Netherlands ($4.67B), and France ($4.45B).
Location: Ireland borders United Kingdom by land.
Trade: In November 2021, the top exports of Ireland were Medicinal and pharmaceutical products (€5.9B), Organic chemicals (€2.32B), Electrical machinery, appliances etc., n.e.s. (€1.13B), Miscellaneous manufactured articles, n.e.s. (€789M), and Essential oils, perfume materials, toilet preparations... (€787M). In November 2021 the top imports of Ireland were Other transport equipment (€1.24B), Medicinal and pharmaceutical products (€1B), Organic chemicals (€954M), Electrical machinery, appliances etc., n.e.s. (€758M), and Miscellaneous manufactured articles, n.e.s. (€620M).
Destinations: In November 2021, Ireland exported mostly to United States (€4.94B), United Kingdom (€2.04B), Germany (€1.53B), Belgium (€1.28B), and China (€1.02B), and imported mostly from United Kingdom (€1.93B), United States (€1.52B), China (€1.01B), France (€894M), and Germany (€747M).
Growth: In November 2021, the increase in Ireland's year-by-year exports was explained primarily by an increase in exports to United States (€401M or 8.84%), United Kingdom (€390M or 23.6%), and Germany (€279M or 22.2%), and product exports increase in Electrical machinery, appliances etc., n.e.s. (€324M or 40.3%), Organic chemicals (€316M or 15.8%), and Essential oils, perfume materials, toilet preparations... (€182M or 30.1%). In November 2021, the increase in Ireland's year-by-year imports was explained primarily by an increase in imports from United States (€493M or 48%), China (€411M or 68.9%), and Switzerland (€299M or 130%), and product imports increase in Electrical machinery, appliances etc., n.e.s. (€429M or 130%), Organic chemicals (€282M or 41.8%), and Miscellaneous manufactured articles, n.e.s. (€221M or 55.5%).
